  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The XHuman is unnoticeably different to a Human to o=
ther
  alien races, the majority of difference is behavioural however a Human or
  XHuman is able to see the differences through slight genetic characterist=
ics
  common to each race. <br>
  <br>
  Known in Human history as the Relakis incident. Relakis a colony of the
  Humans had been quarantined due to an extremely virulent virus. This
  quarantine lasted many generations and was largely successful at stopping=
 the
  spread of the virus which the population had begun developing genetic
  immunity to. The planet was separated from the rest of the universe in so
  many ways Relakis had become a mostly independent colony. This separation
  also caused the first recorded case of speciation in Human history. Unabl=
e to
  breed with a Human but also noticeably different in behaviour Humans bega=
n to
  dub the population of Relakis Ex Humans as a racial slur. <br>
  <br>
  The 'Ex Humans' quickly adopted this name to describe their race as XHuma=
n.
  Banned from migrating to human worlds because of fear of the differences =
and
  the implications it had for other Humans they quickly separated as a race=
. <br>
  <br>
  The XHuman behaviourally has less inhibition than a Human and they are qu=
ick
  to offend each other because of huge cultural differences. <br>
  <br>
  XHumans and Humans find each other detestable. Something about the extreme
  familiarity, the very close in looks but also noticeably different makes =
each
  race intolerant of each other. Studies have shown this is probably a
  behaviour born from evolution that helps evolution make steps through
  speciation.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The XHumans preferred weapons are Gravitic and they =
have a
  Balanced approach with Energy Research.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>In game term=
s the
  XHuman are a very close match to Humans, with a few minor differences not
  shown with this small preview. They have the same objectives as humans an=
d so
  are a direct competitor if the humans are in the galaxy also. In most Dis=
tant
  Worlds games the Humanoids all get along together and create a powerful
  alliance often dominating games. The XHumans were created to very
  occasionally split up this alliance. Depending on a lot of factors the
  XHuman/Human hatred can split the humanoid alliance apart in conflict. It
  doesn't happen many games but can really mix things up when it does.<o:p>=
</o:p></i></p>
